INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (27426, 'Ultimate Barbarian', 'A 2D top down retro action game with roguelike and RPG elements. You are a barbarian looking for glory, trying to defeat an absolutly tyrannic king and take his thrown. You''ll have to train yourself in a dangerous world, find gold through quests to get better weapons and potions, explore many locations like taverns and dungeons. 
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (5250, 'Ultimate Band', null, '2008-11-24') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (14443, 'Ultima: Worlds of Adventure 2 - Martian Dreams', 'I write these words aboard a colossal bullet rocketing from the Earth to Mars. Wondrous as this is (and it is, I assure you, quite wondrous), I am even more amazed by the fact that it is the year 1895! Tesla - yes, the noted scientist of years past, Nikola Tesla! -- is unsure how long the voyage will take so I have decided to pass the time recording what mankind (circa 1895) knows of our destination - Mars. How I came by this information is a story in itself.', null) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (24951, 'Ultima: Escape from Mt. Drash', null, '1983-12-30') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (2520, 'Ultima VIII: Pagan', 'The Ultima VIII Pagan starts exactly where Ultima VII ended. Avatar is cast to the world of Pagan by the Guardian. In the meantime, the Guardian is taking control over Britannia and Avatar has to find the way to leave Pagan and save Britannia from the Guardian. The world of Pagan is ruled by four titans that prevent any interworld travel. To open a portal to Britannia, Avatar has to destroy all four titans ad claim their power.', '1994-12-30') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (6165, 'Ultima VII: The Black Gate', 'It has been two centuries since the Avatar last appeared in our good kingdom. Some have written that at last it is possible to interpret the tales of the Avatar as they should be, with the proper historical perspective. Some argue that as time moves on, the truth of what actually occurred will fade even further away and that we have a responsibility to preserve the legends as we now know them. However, most agree when it comes to a number of basic theories.
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (9574, 'Ultima VII: Part Two - Serpent Isle', 'This game takes place 18 months after The Black Gate. Batlin, the leader of the Fellowship has disappeared, as well as Iolo''s wife Gwenno. A map is found that points to the Serpent Isle where the Guardian is still planning to destroy Britannia. Lord British sends you, the Avatar, and your companions to this new land. Once there, you discover that a great imbalance is upon the isle and it is up to you to fix it. To do so, you must learn the philosophies of the original inhabitants of this land who worshipped giant serpents symbolizing the principles of Order, Chaos and Balance.', '1993-12-30') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (12230, 'Ultima VI: The False Prophet', 'Though believed to be mythological creatures the existence of Gargoyles was discovered shortly after the first expedition into the geologically unstable underworld. At first, they seemed content to remain in their subterranean domain, but recently they began appearing in our world, seemingly bent on doing us great harm. These diabolical nemeses have begun to seize our holy shrines and places of enlightenment. Scores of homes and villages in our land have been destroyed during nocturnal raids mounted by the daemonic fiends, while countless others stand empty and deserted. 
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (12229, 'Ultima V: Warriors of Destiny', 'After a century of relative peace, the Avatar of Virtue is summoned back to the medieval kingdom of Britannia to deal with a new threat: the usurper Lord Blackthorn, a formerly honorable nobleman who has been corrupted by strange new creatures called the Shadowlords. After the recent disappearance of the true king, Lord British, the realm has fallen under martial law. Blackthorn now rules the land by brutally enforcing the eight Virtues upon the people of Britannia - corrupting their meaning in the process. The Avatar must gather together his former companions, now made outlaws by Blackthorn''s regime, and venture forth to defeat the vile Shadowlords and recover the true king from the shadowy depths of the Underworld.', '1988-12-30') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (12908, 'Ultima Underworld: The Stygian Abyss', 'The Isle of the Avatar was discovered during the Fourth Age (as related in Quest of the Avatar), at the climax of the Avatar’s quest. The Stranger from Another World, who came to Britannia in answer to Lord British’s summons, completed the Test of the Eight Virtues and became the Avatar — the embodiment of the pure axiom of life.
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (2530, 'Ultima Underworld II: Labyrinth of Worlds', null, '1993-12-30') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (3126, 'Ultima Online', 'Ultima Online is the product of Richard Garriott''s idea for a fantasy game involving several thousand people who can all play in a shared fantasy world. It is responsible for grandfathering the genre of the MMO, and showing the industry that MMO''s were the next era of gaming.', '1997-09-23') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (7083, 'Ultima IX: Ascension', 'Prepare to embark on an adventure beyond imagination with the return of the best selling role-playing series of all time. In the 9th and final chapter in the 20-year legacy you return to Britannia™ for your last epic quest. As the heroic Avatar, only you can save Lord British™ and his people from the evil Guardian who has devastated the landscape and tainted the 8 sacred virtues. Valiant combat, magical prowess and knowledge of the 8 virtues are your weapons against evil in Ultima™ IX: Ascension, the most epic role-playing game ever created for the PC.
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (2878, 'Ultima IV: Quest of the Avatar', 'As an addendum to this work, I, Lord British, would like to speak of the Quest of the Avatar mentioned in these pages. The Quest of the Avatar is the search for a new standard, a new vision of life for which out people may strive. We seek the person who can become a shining example of our nation and guides us from the Age of Darkness into the Age of Light. We have sent this message our to the farthest reaches of the known universe, indeed, we have even spoken across the void of time. Is there One who can complete the Quest of the Avatar? Many have tried already, and have met with partial success, becoming enlightened in one or more of the Eight Virtues of the Avatar - but none have yet attained the true state of being an Avatar. 
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (2867, 'Ultima III: Exodus', 'Eons ago Lord British came unto the lands of Sosaria. Since that time it has been united under his rule as the Kingdom of Britannia and has gone through two major crises. A few years ago there were political upheavals among the city states of the kingdom. The ringleader of this political instability was Mordain, the Magician. Under his horrible rule, the people''s lives were devastated. A valiant warrior was called forth from another world by Lord British. This warrior overthrew Mordain.
