INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (22792, 'Princess Connect!', null, '2015-05-25') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (837, 'Prince of Persia: Warrior Within', 'Prince of Persia: Warrior Within is a video game and sequel to Prince of Persia: The Sands of Time. Warrior Within was developed and published by Ubisoft, and released on December 2, 2004 for the Xbox, PlayStation 2, GameCube, and Microsoft Windows. It picks up where The Sands of Time left off, adding new features, specifically, options in combat. The Prince now has the ability to wield two weapons at a time as well as the ability to steal his enemies'' weapons and throw them. The Prince''s repertoire of combat moves has been expanded into varying strings that allow players to attack enemies with more complexity than was possible in the previous game. Warrior Within has a darker tone than its predecessor adding in the ability for the Prince to dispatch his enemies with various finishing moves. In addition to the rewind, slow-down, and speed-up powers from The Sands of Time, the Prince also has a new sand power: a circular "wave" of sand that knocks down all surrounding enemies as well as damaging them. The dark tone, a vastly increased level of blood and violence as well as sexualized female NPCs earned the game an M ESRB rating.', '2004-11-29') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (2437, 'Prince of Persia: The Two Thrones', 'Prince of Persia: The Two Thrones is an action-adventure video game developed and published by Ubisoft Montreal. It was released in December, 2005 in North America for the Xbox, Microsoft Windows, PlayStation 2, and the Nintendo GameCube. It was ported to the PlayStation Portable and Wii, under the title Prince of Persia: Rival Swords with the Wii version utilizing the motion-sensing functionality of its controller, while the PSP version added exclusive content. A remastered, high-definition, version of The Two Thrones was released on the PlayStation Network for the PlayStation 3 on December 21, 2010.
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (836, 'Prince of Persia: The Sands of Time', 'Prince of Persia: The Sands of Time is a third-person puzzle-platformer and action-adventure computer and video game published by Ubisoft. It was released on November 21, 2003 and is a reboot of the landmark video game series Prince of Persia, created by Jordan Mechner in 1989.
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (2468, 'Prince of Persia: The Forgotten Sands', 'Prince of Persia: The Forgotten Sands is a multi-platform video game produced by Ubisoft which was released on May 18, 2010, in North America and on May 20 in Europe. The games mark a return to the storyline started by Prince of Persia: The Sands of Time. Prince of Persia: The Forgotten Sands is the title of four separate games with different storylines. The main game was developed for PlayStation 3, Xbox 360, and Microsoft Windows, while the other three are exclusive for the PlayStation Portable, Nintendo DS, and Wii.', '2010-05-17') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (21267, 'Prince of Persia: The Fallen King', null, '2008-12-01') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (22020, 'Prince of Persia: Rival Swords', null, null) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (22565, 'Prince of Persia: Revelations', null, null) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (23022, 'Prince of Persia: Epilogue', null, null) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (21715, 'Prince of Persia Trilogy HD', null, null) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (21797, 'Prince of Persia Classic', null, null) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (3165, 'Prince of Persia 3D', null, '1999-09-24') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (3164, 'Prince of Persia 2: The Shadow and the Flame', 'In ancient Persia there lived a Sultan who had an only daughter whose beauty was like moonrise in a clear heaven. Now it happened that the Sultan left his kingdom to fight in a foreign land. In his absence, the Princess fell in love with a young traveller who climbed the palace wall to see her. This did not please the Sultan''s Grand Vizier Jaffar who meant to marry the Princess himself. Seizing power, Jaffar had his rival thrown into the dungeons but the young man escaped and struck down the evil magician. When he learned of his Vizier''s treachery, the grateful Sultan offered riches but the stranger requested just one reward. And so the young lovers were wed and they lived happily well, for eleven days. 
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (18129, 'Prince of Persia', 'The award winning computer software adventure that has people everywhere rattling their sabers is here for Super NES. And now the animation is more detailed, and the controls more responsive. There''s even a five part training mode for sharpening your running, jumping, climbing and sword fighting skills.', '2002-09-29') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (2472, 'Prince of Persia', 'The game is set in ancient Persia. While the sultan is fighting a war in a foreign land, his vizier Jaffar, a wizard, seizes power. Jaffar''s only obstacle to the throne is the Sultan''s daughter (although the game never specifically mentions how). Jaffar locks her in a tower and orders her, under threat of execution, to become his wife. The game''s nameless protagonist, whom the Princess loves, is thrown into the palace dungeons. The player must lead the protagonist out of the dungeons and to the palace tower, defeating Jaffar and freeing the Princess in under 60 minutes. In addition to guards, various traps and dungeons, the protagonist is further hindered by his own doppelgänger, an apparition of his own self that is conjured out of a magic mirror.', '1989-10-02') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (2438, 'Prince of Persia', 'Prince of Persia is an action-adventure and platforming video game developed by Ubisoft Montreal and published by Ubisoft. It is part of the Prince of Persia franchise. The game was released in the United States on December 2, 2008 for PlayStation 3 and Xbox 360 and on December 9, 2008 for Microsoft Windows. It was later released on March 24, 2009 for Mac OS X via the Cider engine.
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (7635, 'Primordia', null, '2012-12-04') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (27591, 'Primitive Wars', 'Primitive Wars is a real time strategy computer game developed by Wizard Soft and published by Arxel Tribe', '2001-09-30') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (16507, 'Prime World: Defenders', 'Fight off hordes of monstrous mutants created from a strange cataclysmic event in the new tower defense game, Prime World: Defenders. Join a group of exile treasure hunters who have ventured into the capital of an ancient empire, vast with mystery and danger.
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (15037, 'Prime World', 'Prime World offers exciting heroic battles, waged to prove the superiority of your clan. Collect unique talents and create an army of invincible heroes. Enter into mutual alliance with other clans, for profit and conquest. Raise your clan to the height of its power!', '2014-03-30') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (12722, 'Prime Mover', 'The smoothest, most realistic arcade motorcycle game ever hits the Amiga with the arrival of Prime Mover. Featuring 5 awesome bikes, a huge selection of the most challenging tracks from around the world and realistic and testing riding conditions, Prime Mover screams onto the grid and into pole position ahead of all the competition. So if you want to sample the power and sheer excitement of the international bike racing circuit, then Prime Mover is the clear winner.', '1993-12-30') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (4271, 'Primal Rage', null, '1994-12-30') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (15300, 'Primal Fears', 'Due to a chemical known as pharGONe, the world has been turned upside down. Battle your way through multiple levels, earning upgrades, competing against your friends and more, and find the truth about what has happened to the world.', null) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (17804, 'Primal Carnage: Extinction', 'A class-based online multiplayer shooter unlike any other, Primal Carnage: Extinction features fast-paced human versus dinosaur combat! Will you hunt down human prey as a variety of legendary prehistoric creatures? Or join the mercenary team and make these bloodthirsty beasts extinct for the second time?', '2015-03-04') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (3066, 'Primal Carnage', 'Primal Carnage is an online multiplayer shooter that will engross its players in skilled PVP combat, team-based strategy and savage class-oriented matches unlike any you''ve previously experienced; be it an armed human mercenary or a cunning dinosaur, Primal Carnage is sure to unleash the inner beast in anyone who seeks to survive among the fittest.', '2012-10-28') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (11789, 'Primal', 'Primal tells the story of Jennifer Tate, a 21-year-old woman searching for her boyfriend through a series of demonic realms. As the story develops, more is revealed about Jen''s past and her relationship with her boyfriend, as well as the nature of the demon worlds.
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (2068, 'Pride of Nations', 'Pride of Nations is a turn-based historical strategy game set in the colonial era of the 19th century, where the player takes control of a country and guides it through industrialization, military conquest, and colonization.', null) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (22177, 'Pride and Prejudice', null, null) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (18276, 'Pride FC: Fighting Championships', null, '2003-02-10') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (21337, 'Prey the Stars', null, null) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (14378, 'Prey for the Gods', '"Prey for the Gods is a brutal journey set on a desolate frozen island, where your only chance of survival is to destroy the very gods you believe in.
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (525, 'Prey 2', 'Prey 2 is an open world sci-fi shooter about an Air Marshal, Killian Samuels, who is abducted by a cruel race of aliens. The game was announced as cancelled on October 30, 2014.', null) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (19531, 'Prey', 'In Prey, you awaken aboard Talos I, a space station orbiting the moon in the year 2032. You are the key subject of an experiment meant to alter humanity forever – but things have gone terribly wrong. The space station has been overrun by hostile aliens and you are now being hunted. As you dig into the dark secrets of Talos I and your own past, you must survive using the tools found on the station, your wits, weapons, and mind-bending abilities.', '2017-05-04') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO games (id, name, summary, release) VALUES (546, 'Prey', null, '2006-07-10') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
